{"title_page": "Constituency LA-38", "text_new": "{{Infobox constituency\n|type= Provincial Assembly\n|name=Constituency LA-38 (Kashmir Valley-III)\n|year=\n|abolished=\n|parl_name= [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]]\n|member= Syed Shaukat Ali Shah ([[Pakistan Muslim League (N)|PML-N]])\n|image=File:LA-38 Azad Kashmir Assembly map.png\n|map1=\n|map2=\n|map3=\n|region_label=Province\n|province=[[Azad Kashmir]]\n|district=[[Punjab,_Pakistan|Punjab]](except [[Lahore Division]] [[Attock District]] [[Rawalpindi District]]\n|elects_howmany=\n|electorate=4070\n|previous=\n|next=\n}}\n'''LA-38''' is a constituency of [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]] which is currently represented by Syed Shaukat Ali Shah of [[Pakistan Muslim League (N)]]. It covers the area of [[Punjab,_Pakistan|Punjab]] (except [[Lahore Division]] [[Attock District]] [[Rawalpindi District]] in [[Pakistan]]. Only refugees from [[Kashmir Valley]] settled in Pakistan are eligible to vote.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.electionpakistani.com/azad-kashmir/LA-38.html|title=LA 38 Punjab Kashmir Valley AJK Election Result 2016|website=www.electionpakistani.com|access-date=2019-09-02}}</ref>\n==Election 2016==\n{{Further|Azad Kashmir Election 2016}}\nelections were held in this constituency on 21 July 2016.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.ecp.gov.pk/|title=ECP - Election Commission of Pakistan|website=www.ecp.gov.pk|accessdate=19 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808103453/https://www.ecp.gov.pk/|archive-date=2018-08-08|url-status=live}} </ref>\n{{Election box begin |title=[[Azad Kashmir Election 2016]]: LA-38 (Kashmir Valley-III)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/mobile/folders/1N__F60FsbJrsAA7s0G6Tww8ALhW-fiPo/1SWlmxNtzYkM_YWysh-rt9Ga46j_bnRQW/1ysQ9KU6IIUcH0RmrX3fyfGpdNbIdnaxC?usp=sharing&sort=13&direction=a|title=National Assembly - Google Drive|author=|date=|website=drive.google.com|accessdate=23 October 2018}}</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link\n|party      = Pakistan Muslim League (N)\n|candidate  = Syed Shaukat Ali Shah\n|votes      = 1,082\n|percentage = \n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n|party      = Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf\n|candidate  = Muhammad Shah\n|votes      = 657\n|percentage = \n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n|party      = Independent politician\n|candidate  = Muhammad Asim Shareef\n|votes      = 443\n|percentage = \n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n|party      = Pakistan Peoples Party\n|candidate  = Hafeez Ahmad Butt\n|votes      = 235\n|percentage = \n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n|votes      = 2,417\n|percentage =\n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n\n{{Pakistan-gov-stub}}\n[[Category:Government of Azad Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Constituencies of Pakistan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox constituency\n|type= Provincial Assembly\n|name=Constituency LA-38 (Kashmir Valley-III)\n|year=\n|abolished=\n|parl_name= [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]]\n|member= Syed Shaukat Ali Shah ([[Pakistan Muslim League (N)|PML-N]])\n|image=File:LA-38 Azad Kashmir Assembly map.png\n|map1=\n|map2=\n|map3=\n|region_label=Province\n|province=[[Azad Kashmir]]\n|district=[[Punjab,_Pakistan|Punjab]](except [[Lahore Division]] [[Attock District]] [[Rawalpindi District]]\n|elects_howmany=\n|electorate=4070\n|previous=\n|next=\n}}\n'''LA-38''' is a constituency of [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]] which is currently represented by Syed Shaukat Ali Shah of [[Pakistan Muslim League (N)]]. It covers the area of [[Punjab,_Pakistan|Punjab]] (except [[Lahore Division]] [[Attock District]] [[Rawalpindi District]] in [[Pakistan]]. Only refuges from [[Kashmir Valley]] settled in Pakistan are eligible to vote.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.electionpakistani.com/azad-kashmir/LA-38.html|title=LA 38 Punjab Kashmir Valley AJK Election Result 2016|website=www.electionpakistani.com|ac